cs.DC, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.SE, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on modelling and characterizing big data and AI workloads, which often involve distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper specifically mentions AI workloads and proposes a new approach to modelling them. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is another possible category as big data often involves managing and processing large amounts of data in databases. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses implementing the data motifs on different software stacks and developing a benchmark suite. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a new abstraction for capturing common requirements in big data and AI workloads.
